'''Mangū Shrine''' (まんぐうじんじゃ) is a {{ill|lt=Shinto shrine|Q845945|WD=Q845945}} located in the Tsukamoto district of {{ill|lt=Kannami Town|Q1203533|WD=Q1203533}}, {{ill|lt=Tagata District|Q1154841|WD=Q1154841}}, {{ill|lt=Shizuoka Prefecture|Q131320|WD=Q131320}}.<ref name="yuisho">[http://www.shizuoka-jinjacho.or.jp/shokai/jinja.php?id=4402077 Mangū Shrine] - Shizuoka Prefecture Association of Shinto Shrines</ref>

=== Overview ===
The shrine is situated on the southern foothills of Moriyama, a small hill located in the center of the rural Tsukamoto area.<ref name="isan">[https://kannami13.sakura.ne.jp/geo-8.html Moriyama] - Kannami Heritage</ref>

It is considered a disputed shrine (ronsha) of '''Fuminashi Shrine''' (ふみなしじんじゃ), which is a {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Shikinaisha|1=UNKNOWN|WD=Q134917286}}.<ref>[https://shrineheritager.com/mangu-shrine/amp/ Mangū Shrine] - Shrine Heritager</ref>

Based on the enshrined deity, it was originally a {{ill|lt=Hachimangū|Q11390939|WD=Q11390939}}, and it is thought that this name later became corrupted into “Mangū.”

=== Enshrined deity ===
* {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Hondawake no Mikoto|1=UNKNOWN}}

=== Auxiliary shrines ===
* Moriyama Inari Shrine – located at the summit of Moriyama.<ref name="isan"/>

=== Notes ===
{{Reflist}}

=== External links ===
* [http://www.shizuoka-jinjacho.or.jp/shokai/jinja.php?id=4402077 Mangū Shrine] - Shizuoka Prefecture Association of Shinto Shrines

